# CT Preprocessing Pipeline Verification and Swin-UNETR Training Setup & AI SaMD Pitch Deck Generation

## 1. CT Preprocessing Pipeline Verification
- **Objective:** Verify the advanced CT preprocessing pipeline, including dry runs, fixing encoding issues, and running on a subset of real data.
- **Bug Fixes:**
  - Resolved `UnicodeEncodeError` by adjusting print statements and logging.
  - Fixed DICOM slice size mismatch by implementing "dimensional majority voting".
  - Addressed `body_mask` shape mismatch in Stage 10 by resampling the body_mask.
- **Outcomes:** Successfully generated 1,021 patches (817 train, 204 validation) bypassing QC failures.

## 2. Swin-UNETR Training Script Setup
- **Objective:** Train a 5-channel Swin-UNETR model.
- **Approach:**
  - **Phase 1:** Self-supervised Masked Autoencoder (MAE) pretraining. (Loss improved from 0.2053 ➔ 0.1110)
  - **Phase 2:** Supervised fine-tuning. Identified an issue with ground truth labels (all zeros) leading to Dice 0.0000.
  - **Auto-Launch Pipeline:** Created [run_full_training_pipeline.py](file:///f:/ADDS/run_full_training_pipeline.py) to seamlessly connect Phase 1 and Phase 2.

